In Westeros, the Targaryen kings were overthrown a generation back by an alliance of three major noble families: the Baratheons, the Starks and the Lannisters.
There is an ancient evil north of the Wall, the White Walkers. The Watch is supposed to stop them, but now without Jon.
Check this link for a brief explanation: https://goo.gl/RfBJHv
Several different fights are fought independently, in the North, in Westeros and almost everywhere
The longest part of the book tells how the noble Stark family deals with conspiracy and court politics in the Seven Kingdoms of Westeros
One of the story lines follows princess Daenerys, one of the last descendants from the previous royal family, as she grows up on another continent
A story in GoT follows Jon Snow, the illegitimate son of Eddard Stark, as he grows up in the north of Westeros
Jon is (or was) in the special military order called the Night's Watch, which is dedicated to protecting the Seven Kingdoms from the dangers beyond the Wall
At the beginning Eddard Stark is the lord of the north, and his friend King Baratheon asks him to be the Hand of the King (like being Prime Minister, but less fun)
The Stark family symbol is a Direwolf and all six of Eddard's kids have one of these giant wolves.
Ned learns that King Robert has a lot of illegitimate children and they all have his dark hair, which is very different from Robert's children with Cersei...
Cersei's three kids look a lot like… Jaime.. Her brother!!! come on!
Before Baratheon was king of the Seven Kingdoms, they were ruled by the Targaryen family, who had the charming habit of marrying brother to sister to keep their blood pure.
At the beginning of the story all the Targaryens are dead except for a young exiled prince – Viserys and her younger sister – Daenerys
While they are in exile, Viserys marries (or sells) his sister to Khal Drogo, a powerful leader of a barbarian tribe
As part of her wedding present, Daenerys is given three fossilized dragon eggs
After Daenerys survives an assassination attempt ordered by King Robert, Drogo decides that he needs to kill his wife's enemies
Drogo gets wounded and Daenerys asks the help of a wise woman named Mirri Maz Duur to try to heal Drogo, but Mirri betrays Daenerys' trust and kills both Drogo and her unborn son.
In response, Daenerys grieves by burning Mirri alive on a pyre.
Jon Snow is Eddard Stark's, illegitimate son, and while Eddard loves him, Catelyn kind of hates him.
When Eddard goes down south to King's Landing, Jon can't stay home. Instead, he joins the military order of the Night's Watch
The Night's Watch used to be a well-respected institution, but now most of them are convicts who were given the choice between losing limbs/dying or joining the gang.
Eddard and Catelyn have two daughters, Arya and Sansa. Sansa, the older child, wants to be a good lady, which is why she names her wolf Lady.
Arya hates sewing with all the ladies, instead, she runs out to watch the boys play with swords
The Stark kids and the royal kids play-fight, but the main message is that Joffrey is truly a little ***, as Jon Snow tells Arya
Tyrion likes reading and in an opportunity he hits Joffrey when Joffrey refuses to pay his respects to the Starks
Jon gives Arya something to remember him by: a sword she names Needle.
Tyrion, Jon, and Benjen head north for the Wall, running into another member of the Night's Watch, a recruiter named Yoren
Tyrion reads about dragons: the Targaryens once had very powerful dragons, and conquered Westeros, but over the years, the dragons became weak and sickly and extinct
Prince Joffrey goes south riding with Sansa and they find Arya play-fighting with sticks with the butcher's apprentice, Mycah.
Joffrey threatens Mycah (with his very dangerous sword), Arya hits Joffrey with a stick, Joffrey goes to hurt or kill Arya, and Arya's wolf hurts Joffrey
At a point Tyrion runs into Jon one last time; although Jon is doing better, he still thinks about the Starks and asks Tyrion to help Bran.
Eddard gives Arya a "dancing instructor" to teach her how to use the sword. This "dancing instructor" is Syrio Forel
Bran is always bored and angry: he's stuck in bed. He's permanently crippled because Jamie throw him down a tower
